{"lemma":"إِمامَيْ","slug":"إِمامَيْ","root":"#.م.م","root_slug":"_-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/_-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"إِمام","root":"أمم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":12},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","prep"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1177"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"prep","gloss":"before, in front of, in the presence of","examples":[{"text":"بَلۡ یُرِیدُ ٱلۡإِنسَـٰنُ لِیَفۡجُرَ أَمَامَهُۥ. ٦. یَسۡـَٔلُ \"أَیَّانَ یَوۡمُ ٱلۡقِیَـٰمَةِ؟\"","english":"But man would fain deny what is before him. 6. He asketh: \"When will be this Day of Resurrection?\""}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"against the encroachment of something","examples":[{"text":"وأصدر خليفة حفتر بحسب كتابه إلى رئيس مجلس إدارة الهيئة العامة للمواصلات والنقل بالحكومة الموقتة بالبيضاء، أمرا بقفل ميناء طبرق البحري في شرق البلاد أمام الملاحة الدولية.","english":"The debuty of Ḥaftar has, as per his writing to the head of the governing group of the public organization for transport and traffic in the provisional government of Bayḍāʾ, issued an order to close the sea port of Ṭubruq in the east of the country for international shipping."}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"in the face of"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"front, place that is before something"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔa.maː.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1177","headword_ar":"اـِمَامٌ","root":"Am","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"learned man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose example is followed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is imitated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any exemplar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object of imitation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as a head, chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leader,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some other person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether they be following the right way or be erring therefrom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) applied alike to a male and to a female: (Mgh, Msb:) applied to a female, it occurs in a phrase in which it is written by some with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) but this is said to be a mistake: (Msb:) it is correctly without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it is a subst., not an epithet: (Mgh, Msb:) or it is allowable with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it implies the meaning of an epithet: (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~apN","text_ar":"اُمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (T, M, K:) the pl. of the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayim~apo","text_ar":"اَيِمَّةْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K, [but omitted in the CK,]) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aA^omimapN","text_ar":"اَاْمِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S,) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afEilapN","text_ar":"اَفعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amovilapN","text_ar":"اَمْثِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivaAlN","text_ar":"مِثَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) but as two meems come together, the former is incorporated into the latter, and its vowel is transferred to the hemzeh before it, which hemzeh, being thus pronounced with kesr, is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S; *) or it is thus changed because difficult to pronounce; (M;) or, as Akh says, because it is with kesr and is preceded by another hemzeh with fet-h: (S:) but some pronounce it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay^im~apN","text_ar":"اَيِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, T, S, M, K,) namely, those who hold that two hemzehs may occur together; (Akh, S;) the Koofees reading it thus in the Kur ix. 12; (M;) but this is anomalous: (M, K:) it is mentioned as on the authority of Aboo-Is-hák, and [Az says,] I do not say that it is not allowable, but the former is the preferable: (T:) or the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay^im~apN","text_ar":"اَيِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aA^omimapN","text_ar":"اَاْمِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amovilapN","text_ar":"اَمْثِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": one of the two meems being incorporated into the other after the transfer of its vowel to the hemzeh [next before it]; some of the readers of the Kur pronouncing the [said] hemzeh with its true sound; some softening it, agreeably with analogy, in the manner termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona bayona","text_ar":"بَيْنَ بَيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and some of the grammarians changing it into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but some of them reckon this incorrect, saying that there is no analogical reason for it: (Msb:) and accord. to some, (M,) its pl. is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAmu","text_ar":"اـِمَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) like the sing., (K,) occurring in the Kur xxv. 74; (M;) not of the same category as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riD~aY","text_ar":"رِضَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) because they sometimes said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAmaAni","text_ar":"اـِمَامَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but a broken pl.: (M, K: *) or, accord. to A 'Obeyd, it is in this instance a sing. denoting a pl.: (M, S: *) or it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=m~N","text_ar":"ا=مٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=mimo","text_ar":"ا=مِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiHaAbN","text_ar":"صِحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibN","text_ar":"صَاحِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayim~apN","text_ar":"اَيِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwayom~apo","text_ar":"اُوَيْمَّةْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, as El-Mázinee says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uyayom~apN","text_ar":"اُيَيْمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_maAmu","text_ar":"الاـمَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Prophet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) he is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAmu","text_ar":"اـِمَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the exemplar, object of imitation, leader,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head, of his nation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAmu AlA^m~api","text_ar":"اـِمَامُ الامَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the exemplar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the nation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M;) it being incumbent on all to imitate his rule of life or conduct. (T.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Khaleefeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) he is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_maAmu Alr~aEiy~api","text_ar":"اـمَامُ الرَّعِيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the exemplar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subjects"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) The title of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_maAmu","text_ar":"الاـمَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is still applied to the Kings of El-Yemen: Aboo-Bekr says, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A_imaAmu Alqawomi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اـِمَامُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is the first in authority over the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAmu Almasolimiyna","text_ar":"اـِمَامُ المَسْلِمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the head, chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leader, of the Muslims."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The person whose example is followed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is imitated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leader,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in prayer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The leading authority"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head, of a persuasion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sect."},{"kind":"text","text":"The four"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^yim~ap","text_ar":"ايِمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay^im~ap","text_ar":"اَيِمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the heads of the four principal persuasions, or sects, of the Sunnees; namely, the Hanafees, Sháfi'ees, Málikees, and Hambelees. And the Hanafees call the two chief doctors of their persuasion, after Aboo- Haneefeh, namely, Aboo-Yoosuf and Mohammad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_imaAmaAni","text_ar":"الاـِمَامَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two Imáms."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The leader"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an army. (M, K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The guide:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) he is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAmu AlA_ibili","text_ar":"اـِمَامُ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leader of the travellers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The conductor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"driver, of camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAmu AlA_ibili","text_ar":"اـِمَامُ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though he be behind them, because he guides them. (M.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The manager,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conductor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right disposer, orderer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rectifier,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (M, K. *) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Kur-án"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAmu Almusolimyna","text_ar":"اـِمَامُ المُسْلِمينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the guide of the Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M;) because it is an exemplar. (TA.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The model-copy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standard-copy, of the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely the copy of the Khaleefeh 'Othmán, is particularly called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_imaAmu","text_ar":"الاـِمَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b11-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The scripture"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any people: and, without the article,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a book,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"written record."},{"kind":"text","text":"] It is said in the Kur [xvii. 73],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawoma nadoEuw kul~a A^unaAsK biA_maAmihimo","text_ar":"يَوْمَ نَدْعُو كُلَّ اُنَاسٍ بِاـمَامِهِمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day when we shall call every one of mankind with their scripture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with their prophet and their law:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with their book in which their deeds are recorded."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) It is also said in the Kur [xxxvi. 11],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~a $ayo'K","text_ar":"كُلَّ شَيْءٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoSayonaAhu fiY A_imaAmK mubiynK","text_ar":"اَحْصَيْنَاهُ فِى اـِمَامٍ مُبِينٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, says El-Hasan, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And everything have we recorded"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a perspicuous book,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Jel;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the Preserved Tablet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lesson"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a boy,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is learned each day"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the school:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~abaqu","text_ar":"السَّبَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The model,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pattern,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a semblance, or shape. (M, K.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The builder's wooden instrument"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rule"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby he makes the building even."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K. *) ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cord which the builder extends to make even, thereby, the row of stones or bricks of the building;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~ur~u","text_ar":"التُّرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmiToharu","text_ar":"المِطْهَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the string which is extended upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against, a building, and according to which one builds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K. *) ―         -b16-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAmN","text_ar":"اـِمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, [but omitted in some copies,] M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a manifest road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in the Kur [xv. 79],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa A_in~ahumaA labiA_maAmK mubiynK","text_ar":"وَ اـِنَّهُمَا لَبِاـمَامٍ مُبِينٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they were both, indeed, in a way pursued and manifest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a way which they travelled in their journeys."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr.) ―         -b17-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taloqaA='","text_ar":"تَلْقَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":") of the Kibleh. (M, K. *) ―         -b18-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tract, quarter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"region, of land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b19-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A string"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a bow or lute &c.]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watarN","text_ar":"وَتَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sgh, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","T","M","K","Akh"]}]}}